            <fr:title text="Monoid structure of endo-relations">Monoid structure of endo-relations</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Corollary</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For every set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, the structure <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}},\mathsf {id}_{A},\circ \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> given by <fr:link href="/jms-00JC/" title="Directed graph" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00JC/" display-uri="jms-00JC" type="local">endo-relations</fr:link> is a monoid.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We have seen in <fr:link href="/jms-00IP/" title="Associativity and unit laws of relational composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IP/" display-uri="jms-00IP" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IP/" display-uri="jms-00IP" /></fr:link> that <fr:link href="/jms-00IQ/" title="Relational composition" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IQ/" display-uri="jms-00IQ" type="local">relational composition</fr:link> is associative and has <fr:link href="/jms-00II/" title="The identity relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00II/" display-uri="jms-00II" type="local">identity relations</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {id}_{A}]]></fr:tex> as neutral elements.</html:p>
